{"id": 224999420, "title": "The Best Is Yet To Come At Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts from Waikiki beach at dusk Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts Tell people you\u2019re going to Hawaii, and you\u2019ll be met with enthuastic questioning, namely: \u201cWhere are you staying?\u201d Tell them you\u2019re going to Waikiki, however, and watch their giddy expressions wane. Ann Hood summed it up best in this 2023 New York Times article: \u201cLately, it\u2019s become fashionable to dismiss Waikiki as a playland for tourists and not the \u2018real\u2019 Hawaii.\u201d My take: are over four million visitors who spend their vacations and hard-earned money in Waikiki wrong? Also, who has the authority to claim what\u2019s authentic and real? As long as you\u2019re enjoying yourself and making memories, that\u2019s all that matters\u2014period. Exterior of Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts Given Waikiki\u2019s popularity as a tourist destination, the competition between hotels is stiff. But if you\u2019re seeking luxury accommodations in a quieter setting that still feels distinctly Hawaiian, consider Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts. Set in the Waikiki Beach Walk complex, the 38-floor tower is walkable to the neighborhood\u2019s top attractions, dining, and of course, sun-kissed beaches, yet feels removed from bustling Kalakaua Avenue. \u201cYou\u2019re staying in a good part of Waikiki,\u201d my Uber driver assured me as we headed there. \u201cIt\u2019s not so noisy or crazy there.\u201d Bryan O\u2019Sullivan Studio is leading Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts' renovation project ... [+] commencing in early 2025. Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts MORE FOR YOU Trump Trial Prosecutor Ends Closing Argument After Nearly 5 Hours Jury Instructions Set For Wednesday Gas Explosion In Downtown Youngstown Ohio Injures At Least 7 Take Advantage Of The Best Memorial Day Laptop Sales Still Live The property was announced in April as the latest member of Hilton\u2019s luxury LXR portfolio, bidding adieu to its former life as the Trump International Hotel Waikiki. Though the overall look remains the same, Hilton has major plans in the pipeline, including a top-to-bottom redesign spearheaded by Bryan O\u2019Sullivan Studio that\u2019s kicking off early next year to align with the building\u2019s 15th anniversary. Taking place over several months, the renovation will include stylish updates to the accommodations, all the public areas from the fitness center to the lobbies, and dining outlets\u2014one of which will soon spotlight a world-renowned chef. Rendering of the ground floor at Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts The good news for those planning a visit to Waikiki this year is that Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach is already a terrific place to stay. While the design throughout the property skews a bit conservative, it\u2019s tasteful and comfortable. The two-bedroom suite I shared with a friend, for example, felt like a true home away from home. In contrast to other hotel suites that claim to be residential based solely on square footage, these sport all the conveniences of home\u2014imagine a fully-equipped kitchen, living area, balcony, and washer-dryer units\u2014so we could work, fix ourselves snacks, and most importantly, fully unwind with peace of mind. And because our suite was situated on a high floor, the views of the beaches and ocean were mesmerizing. A rendering of Wai'olu at Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts Ka La'i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels & Resorts The hotel\u2019s two dining concepts, In-Yo Cafe and Wai\u2018olu Ocean Cuisine, is where the Aloha spirit really shines. Though they, too, will be undergoing revamps, guests can look forward to a breezy indoor-outdoor vibe, one of Honolulu\u2019s best breakfast buffets with Hawaiian staples (mochi pancakes, fresh tropical fruit), and an enticing omakase featuring lesser-known seafood such as the braided and briny kohada. No matter what: order Ilikea\u2019s Mai Tai at least once during your stay here. Based on an award-winning recipe from Waikiki\u2019s first high-rise hotel, this cocktail honors Hawaiian tradition while bridging the past and present\u2014much like what Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach has in store for the future. Follow me on Twitter. Check out my website. Katie Chang Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Given Waikiki\u2019s popularity, hotel competition is stiff. But if you want luxury accommodations in a quieter setting, consider Ka La\u2019i Waikiki Beach, LXR Hotels &amp; Resorts.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/katiechang/2024/05/29/the-best-is-yet-to-come-at-ka-lai-waikiki-beach-lxr-hotels--resorts/", "image": "https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/6654c74ac5f569c0595b0b7d/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&height=900&width=1600&fit=bounds", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:00:00", "author": "Contributor,Katie Chang", "authors": ["Contributor", "Katie Chang"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.143}